.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH NTFY 1 "2026-1-17" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ntfy \- tiny helper to push text to an HTTP notification endpoint

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ntfy [options] < /dev/stdin
br
The command reads from standard input and POSTs (or GETs) the payload to a configurable URL.
It is deliberately simple: no extra libraries, just bash + curl.

.TP
.B s options
.RS
.IP \[bu\] \"-u, --url=URL\"
Specify the destination endpoint.  If omitted the script builds a default URL from
the environment variable \\fI NTFY_TOPIC \\fR or falls back to \fBhttps://ntfy.sh/general\fP.

.IP \[bu\] \"-m, --method=_METHOD\"
Choose HTTP method (GET or POST).  Default is POST.

.IP \[bu\] \"-t, --topic=NAME\"
Set an inline topic name which overrides the value of \\fI NTFY_TOPIC \\(\\) when no
explicit URL is given.

.UE help
Displays a short usage description.

.TP
.B examples
echo "All clear" | ntfy                     # default (ntfy.sh/general)
export NTFY_TOPIC=alerts; echo "Fire!"| ntfy -u https://my.server/api/1  # custom topic
printf '{"text":"boom"}' | ntfy --method POST -m 2>/dev/null   # JSON payload

.SH EXIT STATUS
.RS
.TP
0        Successful upload (HTTP 2xx or 3xx)
.RS
.RE
.TP
1        Invalid usage (missing stdin, unknown option)
.RS
.TP
>1     Curl error (nonâ€‘zero exit code from HTTP request)

